01/04/2011
BELGRADE, Serbia -- The prosecutor's office for organised crime has pressed two more charges against alleged drug trafficker Darko Saric and his group, Special Prosecutor Miljko Radisavljevic announced on Thursday (March 31st).
The first indictment refers to smuggling of 1.1 tonnes of cocaine seized in Brazil in 2008.
The second one is connected to money laundering and investing the money from the drugs in privatisation process in Serbia.
Saric, who is on the run, and his group already face charges for smuggling 2.5 tonnes of cocaine from South America.
(Tanjug, B92, RTS - 31/03/11)
